Date: 0/0/1881
Source: Waitaruna
Author: BATHGATE
Vol / Page: 172
Edition:
Quote:  Meanwhile the `pickers up' were busy gathering up the fleeces as they fell from the bereft sheep and carrying them to the sorting table, where they [173] were stripped of the `pieces', which were thrown aside, while the best of the fleece was quickly classified, rolled together, and deposited in a kind of bin, according to its quality, whether `clothing' or `combing.'
