Vol / Page: 54
Edition:
Quote: The picker-up, commonly called the "fleece-o," collected the shorn fleece, carried it to the rolling table, where the wool roller, after pulling off and tossing the skirts on one side, rolled it and passed it in his turn to the wool classer.
